# Verified Uses

## 2026-07-04 — ProjectHephaestus PR #1833 (issue #1811)

**Context**: Pipeline foundation layer test fixtures. Coordination layer (WorkItem, HistoryEvent) enforces tz-aware UTC timestamps, but test fixtures used naive `datetime.now()`, causing timestamp comparison failures.

**Verification**:
- Files fixed: `tests/unit/automation/pipeline/test_work_item.py`
- Fixtures updated: 3 HistoryEvent test fixtures
- Pattern: `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` instead of `datetime.now()`
- Tests: 58 property-based tests, all pass
- CI: verified-ci (no timezone comparison errors)

**Commits**: Fixed in sub-agent code review response; tested in PR #1833.

## Lesson Applicability

- Used by: Any coordination layer (agents, events, work items)
- Applies to: Test fixtures for temporal/timestamp data
- Scope: Fixture authoring, production invariant mirroring, timezone safety
